Description: Sherd of pottery transport amphora shoulder; flat should with rather sharp turn to wall; near fine red-brown clay with much small mica. Incised inscription.
Curator's comments: Ther shoulder/body angle is more reminiscent of Classical Chian jars, but the graffito is unlikely to be post-Archaic.
Bibliographic references: Petrie 1886 / Naukratis. Part I., 1884-85 (pl. XXXIV, no. 651)
Bernand 1970 / Le Delta égyptien d'après les textes grecs, i: les confins libyques (p. 673, no. 317)
Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JA.049)
